    "body": "@jacqueswww I don't have a good use case in mind. I just worry about changes that make certain checks impossible that currently are not. I want smart contracts to be as versatile as possible and believe there could situations where differentiating between a direct external call and an internal call to a public function is useful that smarter people than me will come up with in the future.\r\n\r\nThe closest use case I have right now is a while back in Solidity I wrote this general purpose DAO that uses an external \"proposer\" contract for voting. The `changeProposer()` function uses the check `require(msg.sender == address(this));` to allow the voting contract to be swapped out for a new one, but only if a vote to do so has successfully occurred on the previous voting contract. In this case the function cannot be private because the DAO can only vote on raw calls. Clearly in this example there are many alternative setups that would provide the same functionality, but maybe there are use cases where thats not true. \r\n\r\n```java\r\ncontract ProposerInterface{\r\n    function executionAllowed(uint256 _proposalNumber, bytes32 _proposalHash) public view returns (bool);\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\ncontract DAO {\r\n\r\n    address public proposerAddress;\r\n    ProposerInterface proposer;\r\n\r\n    function DAO(address _proposer) public {\r\n        proposerAddress = _proposer;\r\n        proposer = ProposerInterface(_proposer);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n\r\n    function execute(uint256 _proposalNumber, uint256 _value, address _destination, bytes _data) public {\r\n        bytes32 proposalHash = keccak256(_destination, _value, _data);\r\n        require(proposer.executionAllowed(_proposalNumber, proposalHash));\r\n        require(_destination.call.value(_value)(_data));\r\n        Execution(_proposalNumber, proposalHash);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function changeProposer(address _proposer) public {\r\n        require(msg.sender == address(this));\r\n        proposerAddress = _proposer;\r\n        proposer = ProposerInterface(_proposer);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nEDIT: What would `callExternal()` return if the change were made?\r\n\r\n```python\r\n@public\r\ndef checkIfInternal() -> bool:\r\n   if(msg.sender == self):\r\n      return True\r\n   else:\r\n      return False\r\n\r\n@public\r\ndef callInternal() -> bool:\r\n   return self.checkIfInternal()\r\n\r\n@public\r\ndef callExternal() -> bool:\r\n   data: bytes[4096] = method_id(\"checkIfInternal()\")\r\n   return extract32(raw_call(self, data, outsize=32), 0, type=bool)\r\n```",
